{{Infobox book <!-- |italic title = (see above) --> | name = Ancient Maya: The Rise and Fall of a Rainforest Civilization | image = Ancient Maya The Rise and Fall of a Rainforest Civilization book cover.jpg | caption = Front cover | author = Arthur Demarest | title_orig = | translator = | illustrator = | cover_artist = | country = | language = English | series = | subject = Ancient history | genre = | publisher = Cambridge University Press | publisher2 = | pub_date = | english_pub_date = 9 December 2004 | media_type = | pages = | awards = | isbn = 978-0-521-59224-6 | oclc = | dewey = | congress = | preceded_by = | followed_by = }}
'''''Ancient Maya: The Rise and Fall of a Rainforest Civilization''''' (2004), an archaeological book written about the ancient [[Maya civilization]]. It was written by [[Arthur Demarest]], Ingram Professor of [[Anthropology]] at [[Vanderbilt University]], [[Tennessee]].<ref name="Ancient Maya - Assets - Cambridge - Cambridge University Press">{{cite web|title=Ancient Maya - Assets - Cambridge - Cambridge University Press |url=http://assets.cambridge.org/.../9780521592246_frontmatter.pdf |publisher=Cambridge |accessdate=15 October 2012 }}{{dead link|date=July 2017 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>
The book discusses the complex lifestyle and amazing political history of the Maya states, from the first to eighth centuries. It also gives an explanation of the mystery of the [[Classic Maya collapse|ninth-century abandonment]] of most of the [[List of Maya sites|great rainforest cities]]. It goes on to conclude that the Maya civilization has lessons for civilization today.<ref name="Ancient Maya">{{cite web|title=Ancient Maya|url=http://www.cambridge.org/gb/knowledge/isbn/item1150608/?site_locale=en_GB|publisher=Cambridge|accessdate=15 October 2012}}</ref>
