{{Orphan|date=February 2009}}
'''Mordkhe Veynger''' (1890–1929) was a Soviet-Jewish linguist.<ref name="yivo">[http://www.yivoencyclopedia.org/article.aspx/Veynger_Mordkhe Jews in Eastern Europe]</ref>

Born in [[Poltava]], Ukraine, he moved to Warsaw. He studied Germanic philology at the [[University of Warsaw]].<ref name="yivo"/>

After World War I he established at Minsk where he became lecturer at the [[Belarusian State University]].<ref name="yivo"/>

He began the first [[Yiddish]] dialect atlas in the 1920s. The atlas is limited to phonology and to Yiddish spoken within the territory of the [[Soviet Union]] in 1931.<ref>Jacobs, Neil. ''Yiddish: A Linguistic Introduction''. Cambridge: Cambridge University Press, 2005.</ref>

